## Prompt-writing rules

- Start prompts with verification, not assumptions.
- Do not tell the model to fix a bug unless the prompt also says to reproduce it first.
- If a bug is no longer reproduced, instruct the model not to rewrite that area.
- Ask for targeted fixes only:
  - exact runtime error
  - exact API 404
  - exact stale copy
  - exact permission gate
- Do not ask for broad redesigns, large internal renames, schema changes, or new modes.
- When requesting UI changes, follow the existing page pattern:
  - use full-page edit only where the page already uses full-page edit
  - use modal/side panel only where the feature already uses modal/side panel
  - do not invent extra side entry forms or duplicate edit surfaces
- Require a final report with:
  - what was reproduced
  - what was not reproduced
  - files changed
  - exact root cause
  - verification result per route
  - remaining risks/follow-ups

## Routes to verify for Community/account work

For logged-in QA, verify these routes or tabs when relevant:

- /Community
- /Community?tab=teams
- /Community?tab=messages
- /Community?tab=people
- /Messages
- /Teams
- /Settings
- /CoachDirectory

Wait at least 5 seconds after route or tab navigation before judging whether the route is
stable.
